# Premium frontend (this repo)

## Layout and stability

- **`next/image`**: Always set explicit `width`/`height`, or `fill` inside a parent with fixed **`aspect-*`** (or fixed height) so nothing reflows when media loads.
- **Embeds / third-party blocks**: Reserve height with **`min-h-*`** (see newsletter placeholders) before scripts or iframes load.
- **Global**: Do not introduce horizontal page scroll; use **`min-w-0`** on flex/grid children that should shrink. Use **`overflow-x-clip` on `html` only** (not `overflow-x-hidden` on both `html` and `body`—Chromium can mishandle trackpad scroll). See [`src/app/globals.css`](src/app/globals.css).
- **Safe areas**: Compose **`env(safe-area-inset-*)`** with layout padding on the shell and nav (see [`src/components/nav/shell.tsx`](src/components/nav/shell.tsx), [`src/components/nav/nav-dock.tsx`](src/components/nav/nav-dock.tsx)).

## Motion (compute-light)

- Animate **only `transform` and `opacity`** for ongoing transitions. Do **not** animate `width`, `height`, `margin`, `padding`, or rely on **`width`**-based progress bars; use **`scaleX`** + `transform-origin` (see [`src/components/reading/reading-progress.tsx`](src/components/reading/reading-progress.tsx)).
- Avoid **`transition-all`**. Prefer **`transition-[transform,opacity,...]`** with an explicit list. Prefer **CSS** over adding **`framer-motion`** unless an interaction truly cannot be expressed in CSS.
- **Tactile feedback**: Primary controls use **`active:scale-[0.98]`** (or stricter for dense icon buttons) with **`ease-[cubic-bezier(0.175,0.885,0.32,1.275)]`** where appropriate (see [`src/components/ui/button.tsx`](src/components/ui/button.tsx)).
- **Haptics**: Use **`triggerHaptic`** from [`src/lib/haptics.ts`](src/lib/haptics.ts) on high-intent actions (theme change, successful search submit, primary form submit when wired).

## Server vs client

- Default to **React Server Components**. Add **`"use client"`** only for real interactivity (nav, theme, search, reading aids, form controls, Base UI primitives).

## Loading and perceived performance

- For deferred or streamed UI, use **`<Suspense>`** with a **skeleton that matches final layout** — reuse [`src/components/skeletons/`](src/components/skeletons/) patterns (e.g. [`PostCardSkeleton`](src/components/skeletons/post-card-skeleton.tsx), [`SearchResultsGridSkeleton`](src/components/skeletons/search-results-grid-skeleton.tsx)). Avoid blank fallbacks and generic spinners for page-level content.

## Typography and tokens

- Prefer fluid tokens: **`text-hero`**, **`text-page`**, **`text-section`**, **`text-subsection`**, **`text-lead`**, **`text-prose`** from [`src/app/globals.css`](src/app/globals.css) for headings and body instead of ad-hoc `text-*` steps.
- Keep the palette **monochrome** with **one intentional accent** via existing CSS variables (`--primary`, `--ring`, dark **`--sidebar-primary`** hue); avoid stray hex colors.
- **Cards** use **`rounded-2xl`** via [`src/components/ui/card.tsx`](src/components/ui/card.tsx).

## Nav / glass

- Sticky or fixed nav surfaces use **translucent background + `backdrop-blur-xl`** and subtle **border-white/10**-style edges; align new chrome with [`NavDock`](src/components/nav/nav-dock.tsx).
